          <p><em>Now Playing:</em> Icarus First Cohort Launch Trailer</p>
      </div>
<p>Now, RocketWerkz founder Dean Hall has revealed just how many copies of Icarus were sold during the sale. In a post on <a href="https://x.com/rocket2guns/status/2010559063088934997?s=46" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">X</a>, Hall shared that that an enormous 984,000 copies were during this sales period. On top of that, the game's DLC, which includes two expansions and a "pets" bundle, moved a further 243,000 units.</p><div data-embed-type="tweet" data-src="https://x.com/rocket2guns/status/2010559063088934997?s=46" data-has-image="false"><blockquote data-conversation="none" data-mce-disable-toolbar="true"><p dir="ltr">Over the steam winter sale, ICARUS sold just under a million new base game units during the sale (984k). We also did quarter of a million DLC units (243k).</p>  â€” Dean Hall (@rocket2guns) <a href="https://twitter.com/rocket2guns/status/2010559063088934997?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">January 12, 2026</a></blockquote>              </div><p>These sales also led to a huge increase in the game's active player base. According to <a href="https://steamdb.info/app/1149460/charts/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">SteamDB</a>, the game enjoyed a massive spike in players during December 2025, with a peak concurrent player count of 44,120 (compared to 9076 in November). This is the highest concurrent player count the game has had since its launch month, December 2021.</p><p>Dean Hall is no stranger to hugely popular online games - he was the developer of <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/dayz/" data-ref-id="5000-146913">DayZ</a>, a 2012 zombie survival game that tasked players with surviving in a post-apocalyptic, zombie-filled world where other players were just as dangerous as the undead. The game started life as a mod for <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/games/arma-ii/" data-ref-id="5000-38942">Arma 2</a> before eventually receiving a standalone release.</p><p>Steam has already announced dates for the <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/when-is-the-next-steam-sale-date/1100-6532422/" data-ref-id="1100-6532422">next few rounds of sales</a>, through to May 2026. Coming up in January are the Detective Fest from January 12 -19 and the Board Game Fest from January 26 - February 2.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
